# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Reference: https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/etc/pyenv.d/which/system-version
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a verified Pipfile.lock, it could be ignored.
#   pipenv workflows may differ, so choose the best match.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#pdm.lock
